    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="1276"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1276">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_JCS1">J. C. S.</gloss> Files</note>
                <head>No. 1276<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Text Proposed by the United States Chiefs of Staff</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract<note n="1" xml:id="d1276fn1">For the full text
                            of this document, see the enclosure to <ref target="#d1264">document No.
                                1264</ref>. The same language had appeared in drafts of June 14 (see
                                <ref target="frus1945Berlinv01#d600fn1">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps"
                                    >i</hi>, document No. 600, footnote 1</ref>) and July 20 (see
                            the enclosure to <ref target="#d1263">document No.
                        1263</ref>).</note>]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/> Enclosure to <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C. C. S.</gloss> 877/5</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-21">July 21,
                            1945.]</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>6. The following additional tasks will be undertaken in order to assist in the
                    execution of the over-all strategic concept:—</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">a</hi>. Encourage Russian entry into the <gloss
                        target="#t_War1">war</gloss> against Japan. Provide such aid to her
                    war-making capacity as may be necessary and practicable in connection
                    therewith.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
            </div>
        </body>
